Pours a well hazed orange-gold with a scant finger of short-lived head, minimal lacing.
Smells of oranges, melons and crackers, weeds and sweat.
Taste is grapefruit juice, grapefruit pith, cantaloupe, grape, lime, bread roll and peppery spice.  Finishes with an unexpected hint of cane sugar, a long, lingering hop burn to the tongue, and a warming alcohol burn in the gullet
Feel is smooth, medium-heavy bodied, adequately carbonated and semi-dry.
