4.6/5  rDev +3.4%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Grabbed a couple bottles on 12/19/15
First time trying anythin from trillium, so I was hoping the hype was real.
Look: beautiful pour with a cloudy orange creamy looking beer.
Smell: I get peach, little bit of pineapple, a bit of pale malt in the background, but overall a great smelling beer.
Taste: similar to the smell, peach smacks you in the face, in the best way. I get a robust but slight pineapple taste, also a balanced pale malt in the back end.
Feel: My taste buds are to busy taking sip after sip. I get a creamy texture, and also a sticky feeling on the back of my throat. Very addictive beer. Take your time 
But overall for my first trillium beer, I'm very impressed, and can't wait to try the other beers I purchased. 739 charactersBeergasm1, Dec 20, 2015
